The paper proposes a hardware implementation of an approximated PNN algorithm, which is a type of artificial neural network used for classification problems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of memristive crossbar architecture implies that the paper could also belong to the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) sub-category. The paper also deals with the approximation of the PNN weights and the reduction of circuit complexity, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of threshold logic and normalization techniques could also make the paper relevant to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
